Module 35 – Psychological Suppression 🧠⚖️

Core Message

Procedural systems often demoralize litigants as a control mechanism.

⸻

Lesson Introduction

Delays, rejections, and silence can erode willpower. Recognizing this as a tactic helps you resist.

⸻

Teaching Block

1. Identify the Effect
	•	Notice when you feel worn down and why.

2. Separate from Substance
	•	Understand that fatigue is procedural, not personal.

3. Build Endurance
	•	Use smaller, winnable tasks to keep momentum.

⸻

Real-World Illustration

Facing repeated “no jurisdiction” orders, the litigant began filing short, targeted notices to maintain pace.

⸻

Assignment Prompt

Task:
Name one way to counteract procedural fatigue.

⸻

Model Answer (Sample)

Break large filings into smaller, successive submissions.

⸻

Reflection Summary

Fatigue is their tactic; persistence is yours.

⸻

Visual Pairing

Image Concept:
A runner hurdling over stacked “Delay” signs. Caption:
“Stay in the Race.”
